        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc. The first mention in Deut. of a custom practised also by other Semites. Mesha (Moabite Stone, 14–17) records that having taken Nebo from Israel he slew the whole population for he ‘had ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "devoted it",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " to Ashtar-Chemosh’; the same verb as in Heb. To Israel as to other peoples a war was from first to last a religious process (see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
